{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"63f35663-a4cf-475e-a70b-e743f075152d","content":"Here's what to change:\n\n1. **Update NuGet packages:**\n   - Upgrade `NUnit3TestAdapter` to **v5.0.0+** (it bundles Microsoft.Testing.Platform support).\n   - Remove `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` — it's no longer needed.\n   - Add `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.TrxReport` if you need TRX output.\n\n2. **Set the test runner in your `.csproj`:**\n   ```xml\n   <PropertyGroup>\n     <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n   </PropertyGroup>\n   ```\n\n3. **Run tests** the same way:\n   ```bash\n   dotnet test\n   ```\n\n**Key differences to be aware of:**\n- Each test project now runs as its own executable.\n- Some VSTest-specific `.runsettings` options may not apply; check the [Microsoft.Testing.Platform docs](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/core/testing/microsoft-testing-platform-overview) for equivalents.\n- CLI flags change slightly (e.g., `--filter` still works, but some switches differ).","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"d8722994-a92f-4b94-8ef1-b343d2c1aec8","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating their NUnit test project from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform. This is a general knowledge question - I don't need to explore any codebase. Let me provide a concise answer.","outputTokens":351,"requestId":"0839:5FAF2:7DF21B2:8C21A2D:69EABE14"},"id":"3b6c638d-9824-456b-a4b4-9e9939622793","timestamp":"2026-04-24T00:49:32.173Z","parentId":"c7809b2a-5ef2-43c3-8a84-1931545d4b48"}
